## Goal

Produce 4–6 high-confidence CZ↔HCR landmark pairs per subject *without
human input*, mimicking manual workflow steps 2.1–2.3.

The seed constellation has two downstream uses in v2:
1. **Anchor for E.TPS** (v2-S05) — TPS expansion seeded by the K pairs.
2. **Rescue path for v2-S03 ICP failures** — on subjects where the
   gated M3-ICP/C5 ensemble underperforms (755252, 782149 currently),
   the seed pairs may give E.TPS or even a refined ICP a better basin.

